==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Logwood
<hw>Log"wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from being
imported in <ets>logs</ets>.]</ety> <def>The heartwood of a tree
(<spn>H⟦ae⟧matoxylon Campechianum</spn>), a native of South America, It
is a red, heavy wood, containing a crystalline substance called
<part>h⟦ae⟧matoxylin</part>, and is used largely in dyeing. An extract
from this wood is used in medicine as an astringent. Also called
<altname>Campeachy wood</altname>, and
<altname>bloodwood</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-logy</ent>⟦br⟧
